e several others fled into the forest with fatal gunshot wounds” sources said. Troops also recovered 2 Pulemyot Kalashnikova Tankovyi (PKT) rifles and 1 AK 47 rifle. In the earlier encounter which led to neutralization of 32 armed bandits on 3rd February 2021 during a massive clearance operation by operation Hadarin Daji, troops also recovered 16 motorcycles and 2 AK 47 magazines from the criminal elements. Vanguard News Nigeria By Joseph Erunke THE Nigerian Air Force, NAF, Tuesday morning, said its troops deployed in Zamfara State, killed no fewer than 10 armed bandits at Sububu Forest area in the state, yesterday.   The service, in a statement by its spokesman, Air Commodore Ibikunle Daramola, said the success against the bandits… April 23, 2019 In "News" At least 13 armed bandits have been killed by the military under Operation Hadarin Daji in several villages in Katsina, Kebbi and Zamfara States. The Acting Force Information Officer of the Operation, Capt. Abayomi Orii-Orisan disclosed this in a statement on Friday. He said the troops intercepted a large cache… February 22, 2020 In "News" By Adakole Auke - Sokoto Nigeria Army said it has within the months of December last year and January this year killed no fewer than 106 unrepentant bandits, including their commanders, rescued 10 innocent kidnapped victims and recovered 600 rustled cows and 300 sheep in Zamfara state. According to a… January 12, 2020 In "News"